-- BMO Capital Names Dan McNamara U.S. Financial Institutions Head
-- B y   M a t t h e w   M o n k s   a n d   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-11-19T21:16:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-19/bmo-capital-names-dan-mcnamara-u-s-financial-institutions-head.html
Bank of Montreal, Canada’s fourth
biggest bank by assets, has hired former Calamos Asset
Management Inc. executive Dan McNamara to oversee financial
institutions investment banking in the U.S.  McNamara will replace Erik van Nispen as head of financial
institutions for the U.S., according to the bank’s spokesman Pav
Jordan. He declined to discuss Nispen’s plans.  McNamara joined the Chicago office of BMO’s investment
banking arm, BMO Capital Markets, on Nov. 14, according to the
Financial Industry Regulatory Authority. He has been a banker
for about 28 years, and was co-head of Nomura Holdings Inc.’s
global financial institutions in  Hong Kong  before joining
Calamos in a business development role 2011,  according  to a
Calamos press release that year.  He left Naperville, Illinois-based Calamos in August,
according to Finra’s data.  Van Nispen joined BMO in 2005 from Milestone Advisors LLC,
a Washington D.C.-based investment bank acquired by Houlihan
Lokey last year, according to a press release at the time.  To contact the reporters on this story:
